text: Sezza is using Procreate with an ipad to draw Bahamut, a mythological dragon. She is currently working on the lineart layer over a previous sketch. There is also a figure in front of the dragon, but it is not well defined at this point.
She is working on the back feet of the dragon.
The screen is filled with various emotes as a resubscribe comes in.
She is working on the right leg of the dragon.
She uses some distortion effects to change the perspective of the dragon to be more facing the upper right.
She is working on the wings of the dragon now, specifically the right wing.
She has moved onwards to the left wing.
She moves her arms about to more easily see the effects of the lag.
She is working on the figure in front of the dragon now, specifically the long hair.
She is responding to chat telling her that they trust her with her creative freedom.
She has moved on to the figure's cloak/upper clothes.
She is working on the figure's right arm/fingers. They are outstretched facing the bottom left.
She uses distortion effects to make the arm point more towards the bottom left.
She goes back to working on the character's torso.
A raid with a party of five comes in. There is a picture of the rat and soot sprites from Spirited Away on the screen.
